# Clean coding

- Prefer a library that already solves it over a custom 60-line rewrite, if it is maintained and fits the free-tier stack.
- Prefer 10 correct lines over 60 clever ones.
- No unused files, dead imports, commented-out code, or speculative abstractions.
- Name things for the domain (truck, load, score_run), not for patterns (BaseAbstractFactory).
- Trust-boundary validation stays; decorative try/except and logging noise go.
- Secrets only in env / host dashboards — never commit `.env` or API keys.
- Match existing project style once code exists; until then: Django/DRF and React conventions as used in this repo.
